   single kilobyte-per-second band across two orders of magnitude in
   N — the constant-per-node-load property SWIM proved analytically
   for its dissemination component.],
)

// =====================================================================
// 6. Loss tolerance
// =====================================================================
= Loss tolerance

Birman et al.'s Bimodal Multicast paper proves stable delivery
through roughly 25–30% packet loss. Gabion runs the same
configuration (#math.italic[f] = 3, anti-entropy push, frame-level
dedup) under i.i.d. per-link drop up to 50%.

#figure-svg(
  "/target/gossip-bench/figures/loss.svg",
  [Trial-level dots, median crossbar per loss level. N = 16,
   #math.italic[f] = 3, three trials at each drop probability.
   Every scenario converges by the end of the 20-second virtual
   window — no run shows residual divergence. The median round count
   grows by +1 from 0% to 30% loss and by +2 from 0% to 50%.],
)

#v(0.5em)

#table(
  columns: (auto, auto, auto, auto),
  align: (right, right, right, right),
  stroke: 0.3pt + sub-color,
  inset: 4pt,
